The paper involves the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for abnormality detection in musculoskeletal radiographs, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The development of the models involved theoretical study, iterative prototyping, and empirical evaluation of the results, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the workload of radiograph examinations and the need for diagnostic accuracy, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of ensemble models for performance optimization, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
